
[1]latitudinarian

   LATITUDINA'RIAN, a. Not restrained; not confined by precise limits;
   free; thinking or acting at large; as latitudinarian opinions or
   doctrines.

   LATITUDINA'RIAN, n.

   1. One who is moderate in his notions, or not restrained by precise
   settled limits in opinion; one who indulges freedom in thinking.

   2. In theology, one who departs in opinion from the strict principles
   of orthodoxy; or one who indulges a latitude of thinking and
   interpretation; a moderate man.
